                              NERD SCROLL READING MODE

                         A quiet example for books and long text


----------------------------------------------------------------------
CHAPTER 1
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The screen does not have to look like code.

Sometimes the best Nerd Scroll pack is simply a readable passage that moves
slowly enough for a person to follow. A public-domain book, a journal, a
study note, a Bible chapter, a poem you wrote yourself, or a campfire story
can all become part of the same cinematic terminal flow.

The trick is spacing.

Do not paste one giant wall of text.

Give the reader room.

Give the eye a place to rest.

Use chapter cards.
Use short paragraphs.
Use blank lines.
Use gentle section breaks.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
HOW TO BUILD A BOOK PACK
----------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Start with metadata at the top.

2. Add a chapter title.

3. Break long paragraphs into smaller pieces.

4. Keep the lines narrow enough for a terminal window.

5. Use slow or normal speed.

6. End with a clear loop marker if you want it to repeat.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
EXAMPLE PASSAGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The old machine waited beside the desk, quiet except for the soft pulse of
its cursor. It did not shout for attention. It did not flash a thousand
buttons. It simply opened a black window and began to move text across the
screen like a lantern moving through a dark hallway.

Line by line, the page became motion.

A book became atmosphere.

A note became a display.

A story became something you could leave running beside you while you worked.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
USE CASES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Public-domain books
Personal writing
Study notes
Tabletop campaign lore
Relaxing bedtime text
Scripture passages from a license-safe source
Poetry
Affirmation cards
Lecture notes
Story drafts

----------------------------------------------------------------------
STYLE IDEAS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

For a mystery book, add case-file dividers.

For fantasy lore, add map borders.

For scripture, keep the source wording exact and make the text easy to read.

For a study pack, add definitions and section markers.

For a bedtime pack, use slow speed and extra spacing.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
LOOP
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This is the simplest kind of Nerd Scroll pack:

words
space
rhythm
motion

When this reaches the end, it can begin again like a book left open under a
small green lamp.
